## Intent

Position South Africa as a credible and attractive export market for Ugandan coffee.

## Visible Text

### South African Coffee Market Opportunity

South Africa imported approximately 22.7 million kilograms of green coffee during 2024, demonstrating continued reliance on imported supply.

Local coffee production remains relatively small compared to national consumption, creating ongoing demand for imported coffee origins.

Uganda already participates in this market and is recognised as one of the leading African coffee origins supplying South Africa.

### Why This Matters

The opportunity is not creating demand for Ugandan coffee.

The opportunity is expanding participation within an established import market.

